# Frontend `src/**` (single scoped rule — prefer this over @-mentioning long AGENTS.md)

## Stack & commands

- **Stack:** SvelteKit + Svelte 5 + TypeScript.
- **Commands:** `pnpm run dev`, `pnpm run check`, `pnpm run build`.

## Routes and modules

- **Pages / layouts:** `src/routes/` (`+page.svelte`, `+layout.svelte`, optional `+page.ts`).
- **Shared code:** `src/lib/` — use **Svelte 5** runes as in existing files.
- **Modules list** in dev: `/api/v1/modules` (Vite proxy in `vite.config.ts`). Keep API types aligned with backend when contracts change.

## Shadcn-Svelte (vendored UI)

- **Primitives:** `src/lib/components/ui/*` — managed with **Shadcn-Svelte CLI**; prefer minimal direct edits.
- **App components:** `src/lib/components/*` (not under `ui/`) — compose primitives; add domain behavior.
- **Use primitives directly** when not customized; add wrappers only for app-wide defaults or shared behavior.
- **Vendor refresh:** branch `chore/ui-vendor-update-YYYY-MM`; update **one** component at a time with overwrite; run `pnpm run check` after each.

## i18n

- Use `t()` from `$lib/i18n` for user-facing text.
- Messages: `src/lib/i18n/messages/*.json` — when adding/changing keys, update **all** locale files.

## User-visible errors (impact + tags)

All errors shown in panel/toasts must carry an **impact** level (not “priority”): `CRITICAL` | `HIGH` | `MEDIUM` | `LOW`.

- **Codes:** stable `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` (e.g. `LIST_FAILED`, `DATABASE_UNAVAILABLE`). Put HTTP codes / details in **tags**, not in the localized message body.
- **i18n:** use `scopeKey` / `messageKey`; avoid hardcoded mixed-language strings.
- **UI:** map impacts to consistent colors/icons (CRITICAL → red/stop, HIGH → amber, MEDIUM → blue, LOW → green).

## API & backend availability

- Types: `src/lib/api-types.ts`. **All** `/api/v1/*` app calls through `apiFetch` / `apiFetchWithTimeout` from `$lib/api` (offline gate).
- Health / recovery: `probeHealth()` in `$lib/backend-availability.ts` (bypasses gate). **AbortError** must not mark backend offline.

## Icons

No raster icons for UI (`.png`/`.jpg`/etc.); prefer SVG, Lucide, or CSS.

## Deeper conventions

Longer patterns (forms, tables, nav, dev server etiquette): **`docs/agent/patterns.md`**.
